Member of the Australian Workers' Union, Member of Redcliffe RSL, Member of Redcliffe Leagues Club, Member of Lions of Redcliffe Kippa-Ring, Member of Dugongs, Member of Bramble Bay Bowls Club, Member of Queensland Blue Light Association Incorporated - Bronze Member, Patron of Rotary Sunrise Shelta Pak, Patron of Redcliffe Relay for Life (Cancer Council), Qantas Chairman's Lounge Membership (Complimentary), Virgin Blue Velocity Gold Membership (Complimentary)

Attended the AWU National Conference at the Gold Coast, Queensland from February 11 to 15, 2011 inclusive. Invited to be a guest speaker at the AWU Women's Workshop and attend functions over the period. Accommodation provided by the AWU. Invited guests to the AWU 125th Anniversary Dinner on Monday, 13 February 2011.

disclosures.entity: Australian Political Exchange Council and the Korea Foundation
disclosures.details: Attended a delegation of young political representatives to the Republic of Korea. The delegation departed Australia, Friday 24th of June 2011 and returned to Australia on Saturday, 2 July 2011. All travel, accommodation and hospitality expenses were met by the Australian Political Exchange Council and the Korea Foundation. Gifts were presented, including items such as business card holder, decorative pencil case, letter opener, and other small items. Also provided was a small digital photo frame.
On a Parliamentary Delegation to the United States, my husband and I received, from QANTAS Airlines, an upgrade from Business to First Class on our flight from Sydney to Los Angeles.
On 12 September 2011, I attended the PCYC Gala Evening as a guest of the Redcliffe PCYC.
Purchased real estate in Clontarf, Queensland as an investment property.
Entered into an additional mortgage with Suncorp.

I represented the Minister at the A-League Football Final at Suncorp Stadium, Brisbane on 22nd of April, 2012. Football Federation Australia provided complimentary tickets to myself and my husband and two children to attend the event, as the representative.
I received two complimentary tickets by The Redcliffe Musical Theatre to the opening night of the musical production of "Singing in the Rain" at the Redcliffe Cultural Centre on 20th April, 2012.
I received two complimentary tickets to the "Yes, Prime Minister" play at the Playhouse QPAC. The tickets were provided by The Shock Factor Publicity.

Brisbane Airport Corporation has sponsored the Petrie Future Leaders Competition through a donation of a Flight Centre Gift Card to the value of $1000. This Gift Card was redeemed on 15 August 2012 to purchase four flights for the two winners and two parents, from Brisbane to Canberra return, to attend a parliamentary sitting day.
I received two complimentary tickets by The Redcliffe Musical Theatre to the opening night of the musical production of "Pirates of Pensance" at the Redcliffe Cultural Centre on 10th August, 2012.
I received a voucher to the value of $320 from Life In Bloom Photography as a prize at a charity event on 11th August, 2012.
I received two complimentary tickets by The Redcliffe Musical Theatre's A Night of the Proms at the Redcliffe Cultural Centre on 22nd March, 2013.
On 23 April 2013, I accepted an invitation from Virgin Australia to upgrade membership to The Club status for both myself and my husband, George D'Ath.
I accepted two tickets from the Redcliffe Musical Theatre to attend the opening night performance of the Little Shop of Horrors on Friday 19 July 2013.

I received a New Zealand ICC World Twenty20 England 2009 shirt with some player signatures as a prize in raffle by the Redcliffe and Districts Cricket Club at the Einbunpin Festival on Sunday 28 July 2013.
I accepted two tickets to the 'Armed Man' choral and orchestral performance at Grace Lutheran College on Sunday 4 August 2013.
I received a Homemaker 7 piece knife block set as a prize at a charity Cent Auction on 27 July 2013.
